Individual source code files may list additional copyright holders and/or a deviating license. Please check the source code file's header for a possibly deviating license agreement.

In case a source code file has a header that includes my name and only my name (Steffen Itterheim) followed by the "Copyright __MyCompanyName__ xxxx. All rights reserved." statement in the next line, as in this example:
	//  Created by Steffen Itterheim on xx.xx.xx.
	//  Copyright __MyCompanyName__ xxxx. All rights reserved.
In that case please consider that file under MIT License too. This is merely an instance where I didn't clean up the header that is automatically created by Xcode.


